nwAtMibRevText.name: nwAtMibRevText
nwAtMibRevText.description: Indicates the current revision level of the Cabletron at Routing Services MIB in textual format.

nwAtSysRouterId.name: nwAtSysRouterId
nwAtSysRouterId.description: The AppleTalk node address used to uniquely identify the host (device) running the AppleTalk Routing Services. The value of nwAtSysRouterId is equal to the highest AppleTalk node address assigned to any router port.

nwAtSysAdminSTATUS.name: nwAtSysAdminSTATUS
nwAtSysAdminSTATUS.description: Sets the administrative state of AppleTalk Routing Services system wide. Enabled (3) causes AppleTalk Routing Services to become active on all router ports configured and enabled for AppleTalk Routing Services. Disabled (2) causes AppleTalk Routing Services to become inactive system-wide.

nwAtSysOperSTATUS.name: nwAtSysOperSTATUS
nwAtSysOperSTATUS.description: Indicates the operating condition of AppleTalk Routing Services system- wide. The value of nwAtSysOperStatus indicates any problem with your AppleTalk Routing Services configuration. A value of 6 indicates that regardless of the value of nwAtSysAdminStatus, AppleTalk Routing Services is not operating because of an invalid configuration.

nwAtSysAdminReset.name: nwAtSysAdminReset
nwAtSysAdminReset.description: Resets AppleTalk Routing Services system-wide. Reset (2) forces a restart of AppleTalk Routing Services without a graceful shutdown on any active router ports and without affecting any other routing services.

nwAtSysOperationalTime.name: nwAtSysOperationalTime
nwAtSysOperationalTime.description: Indicates the elapsed time, in hundredths of a second, that nwAtSysOperStatus has been in its current state.

nwAtSysVersion.name: nwAtSysVersion
nwAtSysVersion.description: Indicates the current revision level of the AppleTalk Routing Services firmware, in textual format.

nwAtFwdCtrAdminSTATUS.name: nwAtFwdCtrAdminSTATUS
nwAtFwdCtrAdminSTATUS.description: Sets the administrative state of the aggregate (system-wide) AppleTalk packet and byte counters. Enabled (3) causes these counters to become active. Disabled (2) causes these counters to become inactive.

nwAtFwdCtrReset.name: nwAtFwdCtrReset
nwAtFwdCtrReset.description: Reset(2) resets the aggregate (system-wide) AppleTalk packet and byte counters. Reset (2) resets the AppleTalk aggregate counters to 0.nwAtFwdCtrOperationalTime is also reset to 0.

nwAtFwdCtrOperationalTime.name: nwAtFwdCtrOperationalTime
nwAtFwdCtrOperationalTime.description: Indicates the elapsed time, in hundredths of a second, that nwAtFwdCtrAdminStatus has been in the current state.

nwAtFwdCtrInPkts.name: nwAtFwdCtrInPkts
nwAtFwdCtrInPkts.description: Indicates the total number of AppleTalk packets that have been received, system-wide, during nwAtFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwAtFwdCtrOutPkts.name: nwAtFwdCtrOutPkts
nwAtFwdCtrOutPkts.description: Indicates the total number of AppleTalk packets that have been transmitted, system-wide, during nwAtFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwAtFwdCtrFwdPkts.name: nwAtFwdCtrFwdPkts
nwAtFwdCtrFwdPkts.description: Indicates the total number of AppleTalk packets that have been forwarded, system-wide, during nwAtFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwAtFwdCtrFilteredPkts.name: nwAtFwdCtrFilteredPkts
nwAtFwdCtrFilteredPkts.description: Indicates the total number of AppleTalk packets that have been administratively filtered, system-wide, during nwAtFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwAtFwdCtrDiscardPkts.name: nwAtFwdCtrDiscardPkts
nwAtFwdCtrDiscardPkts.description: Indicates the total number of AppleTalk packets that have been discarded, system-wide, during nwAtFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwAtFwdCtrAddrErrPkts.name: nwAtFwdCtrAddrErrPkts
nwAtFwdCtrAddrErrPkts.description: Indicates the total number of AppleTalk packets that have been discarded, system-wide, during nwAtFwdCtrOperationalTime because of addressing errors in the AppleTalk header.

nwAtFwdCtrLenErrPkts.name: nwAtFwdCtrLenErrPkts
nwAtFwdCtrLenErrPkts.description: Indicates the total number of AppleTalk packets that have been discarded, system-wide, during nwAtFwdCtrOperationalTime, because an invalid packet length is contained in the AppleTalk header.

nwAtFwdCtrHdrErrPkts.name: nwAtFwdCtrHdrErrPkts
nwAtFwdCtrHdrErrPkts.description: Indicates the total number of at packets that have been discarded, device-wide, during nwAtFwdCtrOperationalTime, because of an invalid at header.

nwAtFwdCtrInBytes.name: nwAtFwdCtrInBytes
nwAtFwdCtrInBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the AppleTalk packets that have been received, system-wide, during nwAtFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwAtFwdCtrOutBytes.name: nwAtFwdCtrOutBytes
nwAtFwdCtrOutBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the AppleTalk packets that have been transmitted, system-wide, during nwAtFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwAtFwdCtrFwdBytes.name: nwAtFwdCtrFwdBytes
nwAtFwdCtrFwdBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the AppleTalk packets that have been forwarded, system-wide, during nwAtFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwAtFwdCtrFilteredBytes.name: nwAtFwdCtrFilteredBytes
nwAtFwdCtrFilteredBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the AppleTalk packets that have been administratively filtered, system-wide, during nwAtFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwAtFwdCtrDiscardBytes.name: nwAtFwdCtrDiscardBytes
nwAtFwdCtrDiscardBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the AppleTalk packets that have been discarded, system wide, during nwAtFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwAtFwdCtrHostInPkts.name: nwAtFwdCtrHostInPkts
nwAtFwdCtrHostInPkts.description: Indicates the total number of AppleTalk packets that have been successfully delivered to the local host, during nwAtFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwAtFwdCtrHostOutPkts.name: nwAtFwdCtrHostOutPkts
nwAtFwdCtrHostOutPkts.description: Indicates the total number of AppleTalk packets that have been transmitted by the local host, during nwAtFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwAtFwdCtrHostDiscardPkts.name: nwAtFwdCtrHostDiscardPkts
nwAtFwdCtrHostDiscardPkts.description: Indicates the total number of AppleTalk packets that have been discarded by the local host, during nwAtFwdCtrOperationalTiime, due to a lack of host resources.

nwAtFwdCtrHostInBytes.name: nwAtFwdCtrHostInBytes
nwAtFwdCtrHostInBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the AppleTalk packets that have been received by the local host, during nwAtFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwAtFwdCtrHostOutBytes.name: nwAtFwdCtrHostOutBytes
nwAtFwdCtrHostOutBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the AppleTalk packets that have been transmitted by the local host, during nwAtFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwAtFwdCtrHostDiscardBytes.name: nwAtFwdCtrHostDiscardBytes
nwAtFwdCtrHostDiscardBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the AppleTalk packets that have been discarded by the local host, during nwAtFwdCtrOperationalTime, due to a lack of host resources.

nwAtFwdIfTable.name: nwAtFwdIfTable
nwAtFwdIfTable.description: This table contains an entry for each router port. This table is indexed by nwAtFwdIfIndex, which indicates the value of MIB 2 ifindex, which identifies the router port for which each entry exists.

nwAtFwdIfEntry.name: nwAtFwdIfEntry
nwAtFwdIfEntry.description: Each entry specifies the AppeTalk Routing Services configuration for the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtFwdIfIndex.name: nwAtFwdIfIndex
nwAtFwdIfIndex.description: Indicates the value of the MIB 2 ifIndex, which identifies the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtFwdIfAdminSTATUS.name: nwAtFwdIfAdminSTATUS
nwAtFwdIfAdminSTATUS.description: Sets the administrative state of AppleTalk Routing Services on the router port for which the entry exists. Enabled (3) causes AppleTalk Routing Services to become active. Disabled (2) causes it to become inactive.

nwAtFwdIfOperSTATUS.name: nwAtFwdIfOperSTATUS
nwAtFwdIfOperSTATUS.description: Indicates the current operating condition of AppleTalk Routing Services on the AppleTalk router port for which the entry exists. The value of nwAtFwdIfOperStatus indicates any problem with the configuration of AppleTalk Routing Services on the router port. A value of 6 indicates that regardless of the state of nwAtFwdIfAdminStatus AppleTalk Routing Services is not operating because of an invalid port-level configuration.

nwAtFwdIfOperationalTime.name: nwAtFwdIfOperationalTime
nwAtFwdIfOperationalTime.description: Indicates the elapsed time, in hundredths of a second, that nwAtFwdIfOper Status has been in its current state.

nwAtFwdIfControl.name: nwAtFwdIfControl
nwAtFwdIfControl.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs. Setting this object has no effect.

nwAtFwdIfMtu.name: nwAtFwdIfMtu
nwAtFwdIfMtu.description: Specifies the Maximum Transmissions Unit (MTU) for AppleTalk packets on the router port for which the entry exists. This includes the AppleTalk header and data, but does not include framing.

nwAtFwdIfForwarding.name: nwAtFwdIfForwarding
nwAtFwdIfForwarding.description: Controls forwarding of AppleTalk packets on the AppleTalk router port for which the entry exists. Enabled (3) causes AppleTalk packets to be forwarded. Disabled (2) prevents AppleTalk packets from being forwarded.

nwAtFwdIfFrameType.name: nwAtFwdIfFrameType
nwAtFwdIfFrameType.description: Specifies the framing type for AppleTalk packets forwarded on the router port for which the entry exists. Some frame types are only valid for specific media types. The comments reflect those valid media types.

nwAtFwdIfAclIdentifier.name: nwAtFwdIfAclIdentifier
nwAtFwdIfAclIdentifier.description: Specifies the Access Control ID of the access control list in effect for AppleTalk packets being routed on the router port for which the entry exists. A value of 0 indicates that no access control list is in effect.

nwAtFwdIfAclSTATUS.name: nwAtFwdIfAclSTATUS
nwAtFwdIfAclSTATUS.description: Controls the operation of any access control list configured for AppleTalk traffic on the router port for which the entry exists. Enabled (3) applies the access control list indicated by the value of nwAtFwdIfAclIdentifier to all AppleTalk traffic being routed on the port. Disabled (2) prevents the access control list from being applied.

nwAtFwdIfCacheControl.name: nwAtFwdIfCacheControl
nwAtFwdIfCacheControl.description: Controls AppleTalk Address caching on the router port for which the entry exists. When AppleTalk Address caching is enabled, AppleTalk Addresses used for address validation, filtering, and forwarding are stored in the cache. This cache is checked first before doing a full route table lockup, which speeds up the switching process. Enabled (3) turns on AppleTalk Address caching. Disabled (2) turns it off.

nwAtFwdIfCacheEntries.name: nwAtFwdIfCacheEntries
nwAtFwdIfCacheEntries.description: Indicates the number of entries in the AppleTalk Address cache on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtFwdIfCacheHits.name: nwAtFwdIfCacheHits
nwAtFwdIfCacheHits.description: Indicates the number of times entries in the AppleTalk Address cache have been used to provide the AppleTalk address required to validate, filter, or forward an AppleTalk packet on the router port.

nwAtFwdIfCacheMisses.name: nwAtFwdIfCacheMisses
nwAtFwdIfCacheMisses.description: Indicates the number of times the AppleTalk Address required to validate, filter, or forward an AppleTalk packet on the router port was not found in the AppleTalk Address cache.

nwAtportTable.name: nwAtportTable
nwAtportTable.description: This table contains an entry for each router port configured for AppleTalk Routing Services.

nwAtportEntry.name: nwAtportEntry
nwAtportEntry.description: Each entry specifies the AppleTalk address information for the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtportIndex.name: nwAtportIndex
nwAtportIndex.description: Indicates a unique value for each router port. The value of nwAtportIndex is an integer between 1 and the total number of ports configured for AppleTalk Routing Services.

nwAtportDescr.name: nwAtportDescr
nwAtportDescr.description: This text string provides a description of the port to the end-user; it must not contain anything but printable ASCII characters.

nwAtportType.name: nwAtportType
nwAtportType.description: The value of nwArPortType indicates which link-layer protocol is running immediately below DDP in the protocol stack on the router port for which the entry exists. The value of nwAtPortType determines the format of address octet stings throughout the entire AppleTalk MIB.

nwAtportNetStart.name: nwAtportNetStart
nwAtportNetStart.description: The first AppleTalk network address in the network range configured for the port. If the port is not a native AppleTalk port, this object will have the value of two octets of zero. Set this value to the first network address in the network range configured for the port.

nwAtportNetEnd.name: nwAtportNetEnd
nwAtportNetEnd.description: The last AppleTalk network address in the network range configured for the port. If the network to which this AppleTalk port is connected is a non-extended network, or if it is not a native AppleTalk port, the value for nwAtportNetEnd will be two octets of zero. Set this value to the last network address in the network range configured for the port.

nwAtportNetAddress.name: nwAtportNetAddress
nwAtportNetAddress.description: The AppleTalk node number configured for the port. This value may be used as a hint for an initial node number used during node-finding. If the port is not a native AppleTalk port, this object shall have the value of three octets of zero.

nwAtportSTATUS.name: nwAtportSTATUS
nwAtportSTATUS.description: Indicates the current state of the router port's AppleTalk configuration. If either nwAtportNetConfig or nwApportZoneConfig are set to (5), conflictAverseSeed, and either the configured network number range or zone name seeded by the port conflict with the settings of a neighbor router, nwApPortStatus will have a value of (6), offDueToConflict.

nwAtportNetConfig.name: nwAtportNetConfig
nwAtportNetConfig.description: Specifies the network configuration type of the port. If the port is not a native AppleTalk port, this object will have an unconfigured (4) value.

nwAtportZoneConfig.name: nwAtportZoneConfig
nwAtportZoneConfig.description: Specifies the zone information configuration type of the port. If the port is not a native AppleTalk port, this object will have an unconfigured (4) value.

nwAtportZoneDefault.name: nwAtportZoneDefault
nwAtportZoneDefault.description: Specifies the name of the default zone for the port. If the port only has one zone, that zone is represented here. If the port is not a native AppleTalk port, this object will contain an octet string of zero length.

nwAtportIfIndex.name: nwAtportIfIndex
nwAtportIfIndex.description: Indicates the value of MIB 2 ifIndex, which identifies the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtportNetFrom.name: nwAtportNetFrom
nwAtportNetFrom.description: When nwAtportNetConfig is set to garnered (2), this variable contains the DDP address of the entity from which the AppleTalk network number was garnered. When nwAtportNetConfig is set to conflictOrientedSeed (1), conflictAverseSeed (5), or softSeed (6), this variable contains the DDP address of an entity which supplied or confirmed the AppleTalk network number. If nwAtportNetConfig is set to guessed (3) or unconfigured (4), or if the AppleTalk Routing Services-enabled device has not received any network number confirmation, this object will be set to three octets of zero.

nwAtportZoneFrom.name: nwAtportZoneFrom
nwAtportZoneFrom.description: When nwAtportZoneConfig is set to garnered (2), this variable contains the DDP address of the entity from which the AppleTalk Zone List was garnered. When nwAtportZoneConfig is set to conflictOrientedSeed (1), conflictAverseSeed (5), or softSeed (6), this variable contains the DDP address of an entity which supplied or confirmed the AppleTalk zone information. If nwAtportZoneConfig is set to guessed (3) or unconfigured (4), or if the AppleTalk Routing Services-enabled device has not received any zone confirmation, this object will be set to three octets of zero.

nwAtportInPkts.name: nwAtportInPkts
nwAtportInPkts.description: The total number of AppleTalk packets received on the port.

nwAtportOutPkts.name: nwAtportOutPkts
nwAtportOutPkts.description: The total number of AppleTalk packets transmitted on the port.

nwAtportHome.name: nwAtportHome
nwAtportHome.description: The value of nwAtportHome indicates whether or not the AppleTalk Routing Services-enabled device, the routing entity, is `homed' on the port for which the entry exists. If the entity is homed on the port, then it could perform NBP (Name Binding Protocol) registrations for services that it chooses to advertise.

nwAtportCurrentZone.name: nwAtportCurrentZone
nwAtportCurrentZone.description: Specifies the current zone name for the port. In general, this is the zone name in which services on the port will be registered. If the port is not a native AppleTalk port, this object will contain an octet string of zero length.

nwAtportConflictPhysAddr.name: nwAtportConflictPhysAddr
nwAtportConflictPhysAddr.description: Indicates the link-layer address of the device which caused nwAtportStatus to be set to off (3). If this address is not available, or if nwAtportStatus is not set to off, this object will be a zero length octet string.

nwAtFwdIfCtrTable.name: nwAtFwdIfCtrTable
nwAtFwdIfCtrTable.description: This table contains an entry for each router port configured and enabled for AppleTalk Routing Services.

nwAtFwdIfCtrEntry.name: nwAtFwdIfCtrEntry
nwAtFwdIfCtrEntry.description: Each entry indicates the current packet and byte count of AppleTalk packets on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtFwdIfCtrIfIndex.name: nwAtFwdIfCtrIfIndex
nwAtFwdIfCtrIfIndex.description: Indicates the value MIB 2 ifindex, which identifies the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtFwdIfCtrAdminSTATUS.name: nwAtFwdIfCtrAdminSTATUS
nwAtFwdIfCtrAdminSTATUS.description: Sets the administrative state of the per-port AppleTalk packet and byte counters on the router port for which the entry exists. Enabled (3) causes these counters to become active. Disabled (2) causes these counters to become inactive.

nwAtFwdIfCtrReset.name: nwAtFwdIfCtrReset
nwAtFwdIfCtrReset.description: Resets the per-port AppleTalk packet and byte counters on the router port for which the entry exists. Reset (2) resets the counters to 0. nwAtFwdIfCtrOperationalTime is also reset to 0.

nwAtFwdIfCtrOperationalTime.name: nwAtFwdIfCtrOperationalTime
nwAtFwdIfCtrOperationalTime.description: Indicates the amount of time, in hundredths of a second, that nwAtFwdIfCtrAdminStatus has been in the current state.

nwAtFwdIfCtrInPkts.name: nwAtFwdIfCtrInPkts
nwAtFwdIfCtrInPkts.description: Indicates the total number of AppleTalk packets that have been received, during nwAtFwdIfCtrOperationaltime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtFwdIfCtrOutPkts.name: nwAtFwdIfCtrOutPkts
nwAtFwdIfCtrOutPkts.description: Indicates the total number of AppleTalk packets that have been transmitted, during nwAtFwdIfCtrOperationaltime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtFwdIfCtrFwdPkts.name: nwAtFwdIfCtrFwdPkts
nwAtFwdIfCtrFwdPkts.description: Indicates the total number of AppleTalk packets that have been forwarded, during nwAtFwdIfCtrOperationaltime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtFwdIfCtrFilteredPkts.name: nwAtFwdIfCtrFilteredPkts
nwAtFwdIfCtrFilteredPkts.description: Indicates the total number of AppleTalk packets that have been administratively filtered, during nwAtFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtFwdIfCtrDiscardPkts.name: nwAtFwdIfCtrDiscardPkts
nwAtFwdIfCtrDiscardPkts.description: Indicates the total number of AppleTalk packets that have been discarded (dropped), during nwAtFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtFwdIfCtrAddrErrPkts.name: nwAtFwdIfCtrAddrErrPkts
nwAtFwdIfCtrAddrErrPkts.description: Indicates the total number of AppleTalk packets that have been discarded, because of addressing errors in the AppleTalk header, during nwAtFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtFwdIfCtrLenErrPkts.name: nwAtFwdIfCtrLenErrPkts
nwAtFwdIfCtrLenErrPkts.description: Indicates the total number of AppleTalk packets that have been discarded, because an invalid packet length was contained in the AppleTalk header, during nwAtFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtFwdIfCtrHdrErrPkts.name: nwAtFwdIfCtrHdrErrPkts
nwAtFwdIfCtrHdrErrPkts.description: Indicates the total number of AppleTalk packets that have been discarded, because of an invalid AppleTalk header, during nwAtFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtFwdIfCtrInBytes.name: nwAtFwdIfCtrInBytes
nwAtFwdIfCtrInBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the AppleTalk packets that have been received, during nwAtFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtFwdIfCtrOutBytes.name: nwAtFwdIfCtrOutBytes
nwAtFwdIfCtrOutBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the AppleTalk packets that have been transmitted, durin nwAtFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtFwdIfCtrFwdBytes.name: nwAtFwdIfCtrFwdBytes
nwAtFwdIfCtrFwdBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the AppleTalk packets that have been forwarded, during nwAtFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtFwdIfCtrFilteredBytes.name: nwAtFwdIfCtrFilteredBytes
nwAtFwdIfCtrFilteredBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the AppleTalk packets that have been administratively filtered, during nwAtFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtFwdIfCtrDiscardBytes.name: nwAtFwdIfCtrDiscardBytes
nwAtFwdIfCtrDiscardBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the AppleTalk packets that have been discarded, during nwAtFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtFwdIfCtrHostInPkts.name: nwAtFwdIfCtrHostInPkts
nwAtFwdIfCtrHostInPkts.description: Indicates the total number of AppleTalk packets that have been successfully delivered to the local host during nwAtFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, that were received on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtFwdIfCtrHostOutPkts.name: nwAtFwdIfCtrHostOutPkts
nwAtFwdIfCtrHostOutPkts.description: Indicates the total number of AppleTalk packets that have been transmitted by the local host, during nwAtFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtFwdIfCtrHostDiscardPkts.name: nwAtFwdIfCtrHostDiscardPkts
nwAtFwdIfCtrHostDiscardPkts.description: Indicates the total number of AppleTalk packets that have been discarded by the local host due to a lack of host resources during nwAtFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, that were received on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtFwdIfCtrHostInBytes.name: nwAtFwdIfCtrHostInBytes
nwAtFwdIfCtrHostInBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the AppleTalk packets that have been successfully delivered to the local host, during nwAtFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, that were received on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtFwdIfCtrHostOutBytes.name: nwAtFwdIfCtrHostOutBytes
nwAtFwdIfCtrHostOutBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the AppleTalk packets that have been transmitted by the local host, during nwAtFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtFwdIfCtrHostDiscardBytes.name: nwAtFwdIfCtrHostDiscardBytes
nwAtFwdIfCtrHostDiscardBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the AppleTalk packets that have been discarded by the local host, due to a lack of host resources during nwAtFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, that were received on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtProtoAdminSTATUS.name: nwAtProtoAdminSTATUS
nwAtProtoAdminSTATUS.description: Sets the administrative state of the AppleTalk distance-vector based routing protocol system-wide. Enabled (3) causes the routing protocol to become active on all router ports configured and enabled for AppleTalk Routing Services. Disabled (2) causes the routing protocol to become inactive.

nwAtProtoOperSTATUS.name: nwAtProtoOperSTATUS
nwAtProtoOperSTATUS.description: Indicates the current operating condition of the AppleTalk Routing Services distance-vector-based routing protocol, system-wide. The value of nwAtProtoOperStatus indicates any problem with the routing protocol configuration. A value of 6 indicates that regardless of the value of nwAtProtoAdminStatus, the routing protocol is not operating because of an invalid configuration.

nwAtProtoAdminReset.name: nwAtProtoAdminReset
nwAtProtoAdminReset.description: Resets the routing protocol. Reset (2) forces a system-wide restart of the protocol without a graceful shutdown on any active router ports.

nwAtProtoOperationalTime.name: nwAtProtoOperationalTime
nwAtProtoOperationalTime.description: Indicates the elapsed time, in hundredths of a second, that nwAtProtoOperStatus has been in the current state.

nwAtProtoVersion.name: nwAtProtoVersion
nwAtProtoVersion.description: Indicates the current revision level of the AppleTalk routing protocol firmware, in textual format.

nwAtProtoStackSize.name: nwAtProtoStackSize
nwAtProtoStackSize.description: Specifies the stack size of the AppleTalk routing protocol thread. In order for a change of this value to take effect, the protocol (nwAtProtoAdminReset), AppleTalk Routing Services (nwAtProtoAdminReset), or the device running Routing Services must be reset.

nwAtProtoThreadPriority.name: nwAtProtoThreadPriority
nwAtProtoThreadPriority.description: Specifies the run-time execution priority of the AppleTalk routing protocol thread. In order for a change of this value to take effect, the AppleTalk protocol (nwAtProtoAdminReset), AppleTalk Routing Services (nwAtProtoAdminReset), or the device running Routing Services must be reset.

nwAtProtoDatabaseThreshold.name: nwAtProtoDatabaseThreshold
nwAtProtoDatabaseThreshold.description: Specifies the run-time maximum number of entries that can be held in the AppleTalk routing protocol route table.

nwAtProtoAgeOut.name: nwAtProtoAgeOut
nwAtProtoAgeOut.description: Specifies the amount of time (in seconds) an inactive entry will be allowed to remain in the AppleTalk routing protocol routing table, before it is deleted, or aged-out.

nwAtProtoHoldDown.name: nwAtProtoHoldDown
nwAtProtoHoldDown.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs. Setting this object has no effect.

nwAtProtoCtrAdminSTATUS.name: nwAtProtoCtrAdminSTATUS
nwAtProtoCtrAdminSTATUS.description: Sets the administrative state of the aggregate (system-wide) AppleTalk routing protocol packet and byte counters. Enabled (3)causes these counters to become active. Disabled (2) causes these counters to be come inactive.

nwAtProtoCtrReset.name: nwAtProtoCtrReset
nwAtProtoCtrReset.description: Resets the aggregate (system-wide) AppleTalk distance-vector based routing protocol packet and byte counters. Reset (2) resets the AppleTalk aggregate counters to 0. nwAtProtoCtrOperationalTime is also reset to 0.

nwAtProtoCtrOperationalTime.name: nwAtProtoCtrOperationalTime
nwAtProtoCtrOperationalTime.description: Indicates the elapsed time, in hundreds of seconds, that nwAtProtoCtrAdminStatus, has been in the current administrative state.

nwAtProtoCtrInPkts.name: nwAtProtoCtrInPkts
nwAtProtoCtrInPkts.description: Indicates the total number of AppleTalk routing protocol packets that have been received, system-wide, during nwAtProtoCtrOperationalTime.

nwAtProtoCtrOutPkts.name: nwAtProtoCtrOutPkts
nwAtProtoCtrOutPkts.description: Indicates the total number of AppleTalk routing protocol packets that have been transmitted, system-wide, during nwAtProtoCtrOperationalTime.

nwAtProtoCtrFilteredPkts.name: nwAtProtoCtrFilteredPkts
nwAtProtoCtrFilteredPkts.description: Indicates the total number of AppleTalk routing protocol packets that have been administratively filtered, system-wide, during nwAtProtoCtrOperationalTime.

nwAtProtoCtrDiscardPkts.name: nwAtProtoCtrDiscardPkts
nwAtProtoCtrDiscardPkts.description: Indicates the total number of AppleTalk routing protocol packets that have been discarded, system-wide, during nwAtProtoCtrOperationalTime.

nwAtProtoCtrInBytes.name: nwAtProtoCtrInBytes
nwAtProtoCtrInBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the AppleTalk routing protocol packets that have been received, system-wide, during nwAtProtoCtrOperationalTime.

nwAtProtoCtrOutBytes.name: nwAtProtoCtrOutBytes
nwAtProtoCtrOutBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the AppleTalk routing protocol packets that have been transmitted, system-wide, during nwAtProtoCtrOperationalTime.

nwAtProtoCtrFilteredBytes.name: nwAtProtoCtrFilteredBytes
nwAtProtoCtrFilteredBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the AppleTalk routing protocol packets that have been administratively filtered, system-wide, during nwAtProtoCtrOperationalTime.

nwAtProtoCtrDiscardBytes.name: nwAtProtoCtrDiscardBytes
nwAtProtoCtrDiscardBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the AppleTalk routing protocol packets that have been discarded, system-wide during nwAtProtoCtrOperationalTime.

nwAtProtoIfTable.name: nwAtProtoIfTable
nwAtProtoIfTable.description: This table contains an entry for each router port. Each entry can contain different values, allowing the routing protocol configuration to vary from router port to router port. This table is indexed by nwAtProtoIfIndex, which indicates the value of MIB 2 ifindex, which identifies the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtProtoIfEntry.name: nwAtProtoIfEntry
nwAtProtoIfEntry.description: Each entry contains the AppleTalk routing protocol configuration for the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtProtoIfIndex.name: nwAtProtoIfIndex
nwAtProtoIfIndex.description: Indicates the value of MIB 2 ifindex, which identifies the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtProtoIfAdminSTATUS.name: nwAtProtoIfAdminSTATUS
nwAtProtoIfAdminSTATUS.description: Sets the administrative state of the AppleTalk routing protocol on the router port for which the entry exists. Enabled (3) causes the routing protocol to become active on the router port. Disabled (2) causes it to become inactive.

nwAtProtoIfOperSTATUS.name: nwAtProtoIfOperSTATUS
nwAtProtoIfOperSTATUS.description: Indicates the current operating condition of the AppleTalk routing protocol on the router port for which the entry exists. The value of nwAtProtoIfOperStatus indicates any problem with your AppleTalk routing protocol configuration on the router port. A value of 6 indicates that regardless of the value of nwAtProtoIfAdminStatus, the routing protocol is not operating on the router port because of an invalid configuration.

nwAtProtoIfOperationalTime.name: nwAtProtoIfOperationalTime
nwAtProtoIfOperationalTime.description: Indicates the elapsed time, in hundreds of seconds, that nwAtProtoIfOperStatus has been in the current state.

nwAtProtoIfVersion.name: nwAtProtoIfVersion
nwAtProtoIfVersion.description: Indicates the revision level of AppleTalk routing protocol firmware on the router port for which the entry exists, in textual format.

nwAtProtoIfAdvertisement.name: nwAtProtoIfAdvertisement
nwAtProtoIfAdvertisement.description: This specifies the periodic interval (in seconds) that the AppleTalk routing protocol agent will advertise routes on this DECnet routing port.

nwAtProtoIfFloodDelay.name: nwAtProtoIfFloodDelay
nwAtProtoIfFloodDelay.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol specific MIBs. Setting this object has no effect

nwAtProtoIfRequestDelay.name: nwAtProtoIfRequestDelay
nwAtProtoIfRequestDelay.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol specific MIBs. Setting this object has no effect.

nwAtProtoIfPriority.name: nwAtProtoIfPriority
nwAtProtoIfPriority.description: Sets the priority of the AppleTalk routing protocol on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtProtoIfHelloTimer.name: nwAtProtoIfHelloTimer
nwAtProtoIfHelloTimer.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol specific MIBs. Setting this object has no effect.

nwAtProtoIfSplitHorizon.name: nwAtProtoIfSplitHorizon
nwAtProtoIfSplitHorizon.description: Sets the operating condition of Split Horizon on the router port for which the entry exists. When Split Horizon is enabled, the AppleTalk routing protocol keeps track of which router port route information is received on, and prevents information about a route form being sent back out the same router port it was received on.

nwAtProtoIfPoisonReverse.name: nwAtProtoIfPoisonReverse
nwAtProtoIfPoisonReverse.description: Sets the operating condition of Poison Reverse on the router port for which the entry exists. When Poison Reverse is enabled, the AppleTalk routing protocol advertises any downed routes as unreachable during the period of time that it must wait before removing the route from the route table.

nwAtProtoIfSnooping.name: nwAtProtoIfSnooping
nwAtProtoIfSnooping.description: Controls the operation of AppleTalk routing protocol Snooping on the router port. When AppleTalk routing protocol Snooping is enabled, the routing protocol operates in passive mode, so that it receives route information, builds and maintains a route table, but does not advertise or send updates on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtProtoIfType.name: nwAtProtoIfType
nwAtProtoIfType.description: Indicates whether the directly connected network segment does or does not support broadcast media access. If broadcast media access is supported, AppleTalk routing protocol advertisements are sent out one broadcast packet per port. If broadcast media is not supported, AppleTalk routing protocol advertisements are sent to each neighbor.

nwAtProtoIfXmitCost.name: nwAtProtoIfXmitCost
nwAtProtoIfXmitCost.description: Sets the cost of transmitting a packet on the network segment connected to router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtProtoIfAclIdentifier.name: nwAtProtoIfAclIdentifier
nwAtProtoIfAclIdentifier.description: Specifies the Access Control List ID of the access control list in effect for AppleTalk routing protocol packets on the router port for which the entry exists. A value of 0 indicates that there is no access control list in effect for AppleTalk routing protocol packets on the router port.

nwAtProtoIfAclSTATUS.name: nwAtProtoIfAclSTATUS
nwAtProtoIfAclSTATUS.description: Controls the operation of the access control list identified by nwAtProtoIfAclIdentifier. Enabled (3) causes the access control list to be applied to all AppleTalk routing protocol packet traffic on the router port for which the entry exists. Disabled (2) prevents the access control list from being applied.

nwAtProtoIfCtrTable.name: nwAtProtoIfCtrTable
nwAtProtoIfCtrTable.description: This table contains the AppleTalk packet and byte counters for each router port on this device.

nwAtProtoIfCtrEntry.name: nwAtProtoIfCtrEntry
nwAtProtoIfCtrEntry.description: Each entry specifies the DECnet Phase IV packet and byte counters on a per router port basis.

nwAtProtoIfCtrIfIndex.name: nwAtProtoIfCtrIfIndex
nwAtProtoIfCtrIfIndex.description: This is the primary index into the AppleTalk interface counter table. This number corresponds to the index into the mib2 InterfaceTable which describes the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtProtoIfCtrAdminSTATUS.name: nwAtProtoIfCtrAdminSTATUS
nwAtProtoIfCtrAdminSTATUS.description: Sets the administrative state of the AppleTalk packet and byte counters on the router port for which the entry exists. enabled(3) causes these counters to become active on the configured AppleTalk router port. disabled(2) causes these counters to become inactive on the configured AppleTalk router port.

nwAtProtoIfCtrReset.name: nwAtProtoIfCtrReset
nwAtProtoIfCtrReset.description: Resets the AppleTalk packet and byte counters on the router port for which the entry exists. reset (2) resets the interface-specific counters to 0. nwAtProtoIfCtrOperationalTime is also reset to 0.

nwAtProtoIfCtrOperationalTime.name: nwAtProtoIfCtrOperationalTime
nwAtProtoIfCtrOperationalTime.description: Indicates the amount of time (No. of time ticks) that the interface-specific AppleTalk packet and byte counters have been active on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtProtoIfCtrInPkts.name: nwAtProtoIfCtrInPkts
nwAtProtoIfCtrInPkts.description: Indicates the total number of AppleTalk packets that have been received, on the router port for which the entry exists, during nwAtProtoIfCtrOperationalTime.

nwAtProtoIfCtrOutPkts.name: nwAtProtoIfCtrOutPkts
nwAtProtoIfCtrOutPkts.description: Indicates the total number of AppleTalk packets that have been forwarded, on the router port for which the entry exists, during nwAtProtoIfCtrOperationalTime.

nwAtProtoIfCtrFilteredPkts.name: nwAtProtoIfCtrFilteredPkts
nwAtProtoIfCtrFilteredPkts.description: Indicates the total number of AppleTalk packets that have been administratively filtered, on the router port for which this entry exists, during nwAtProtoIfCtrOperationalTime.

nwAtProtoIfCtrDiscardPkts.name: nwAtProtoIfCtrDiscardPkts
nwAtProtoIfCtrDiscardPkts.description: Indicates the total number of AppleTalk packets that have been discarded, on the router port for which the entry exists, during nwAtProtoIfCtrOperationalTime.

nwAtProtoIfCtrInBytes.name: nwAtProtoIfCtrInBytes
nwAtProtoIfCtrInBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the AppleTalk packets that have been received, on the router port for which the entry exists, during nwAtProtoIfCtrOperationalTime.

nwAtProtoIfCtrOutBytes.name: nwAtProtoIfCtrOutBytes
nwAtProtoIfCtrOutBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the AppleTalk packets that have been forwarded, on the router port for which the entry exists, during nwAtProtoIfCtrOperationalTime.

nwAtProtoIfCtrFilteredBytes.name: nwAtProtoIfCtrFilteredBytes
nwAtProtoIfCtrFilteredBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the AppleTalk packets that have been administratively filtered, that were received on the router port for which the entry exists, during nwAtProtoIfCtrOperationalTime.

nwAtProtoIfCtrDiscardBytes.name: nwAtProtoIfCtrDiscardBytes
nwAtProtoIfCtrDiscardBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the AppleTalk packets that have been discarded, that were received on the router port for which the entry exists, during nwAtIfCtrOperationalTime.

nwAtFibTable.name: nwAtFibTable
nwAtFibTable.description: This table contains an entry for each route being used to forward AppleTalk data packets.

nwAtFibEntry.name: nwAtFibEntry
nwAtFibEntry.description: Each entry in the table describes an AppleTalk route to a particular destination.

nwAtFibStartNet.name: nwAtFibStartNet
nwAtFibStartNet.description: Indicates the start of the network range for the route.

nwAtFibEndNet.name: nwAtFibEndNet
nwAtFibEndNet.description: Indicates the end of the network range for the route.

nwAtFibNextHop.name: nwAtFibNextHop
nwAtFibNextHop.description: Indicates the full AppleTalk network address of the next hop router for the route. An address of all zeros indicates a directly connected net.

nwAtFibNextHopIf.name: nwAtFibNextHopIf
nwAtFibNextHopIf.description: Indicates the value of MIB 2 ifindex, which identifies the router port through which the next hop node exists. Packets destined for the network specified by the entry will be forwarded on this router port.

nwAtFibHops.name: nwAtFibHops
nwAtFibHops.description: Indicates the number of hops required to reach the destination for which the entry exists. It is considered as metric 1.

nwAtFibRouteType.name: nwAtFibRouteType
nwAtFibRouteType.description: Indicates the type of route (Allows for PPP entries later).

nwAtHostsTimeToLive.name: nwAtHostsTimeToLive
nwAtHostsTimeToLive.description: Indicates the amount of time (in minutes) that an entry can remain in the AARP cache.

nwAtHostsRetryCount.name: nwAtHostsRetryCount
nwAtHostsRetryCount.description: Indicates the maximum number of times AppleTalk Routing Services will retry each attempt to resolve a host address.

nwAtHostCtlTable.name: nwAtHostCtlTable
nwAtHostCtlTable.description: This table contains the control information for maintaining an AARP cache on each router port. Note that the cache entries are maintained by theAppleTalk Address Resolution Protocol Table of the AppleTalk MIB.

nwAtHostCtlEntry.name: nwAtHostCtlEntry
nwAtHostCtlEntry.description: Each entry contains the control information for the ARP cache on the router port indicated by the value nwAtHostCtlIfIndex.

nwAtHostCtlIfIndex.name: nwAtHostCtlIfIndex
nwAtHostCtlIfIndex.description: Indicates the value of MIB2 ifindex, which identifies the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtHostCtlAdminSTATUS.name: nwAtHostCtlAdminSTATUS
nwAtHostCtlAdminSTATUS.description: Sets the administrative state of the AARP cache on the router port for which the entry exists. Enabled (3) causes AARP caching to become active. Disabled (2) causes AARP caching to perform a graceful shutdown.

nwAtHostCtlOperSTATUS.name: nwAtHostCtlOperSTATUS
nwAtHostCtlOperSTATUS.description: Indicates the current operating condition of the AARP Table on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtHostCtlOperationalTime.name: nwAtHostCtlOperationalTime
nwAtHostCtlOperationalTime.description: Indicates the amount of time, in hundredths of a second, that nwAtHostCtlOperStatus has been in the current state.

nwAtHostCtlProtocol.name: nwAtHostCtlProtocol
nwAtHostCtlProtocol.description: Controls the operation of the AARP protocol on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtHostCtlSnooping.name: nwAtHostCtlSnooping
nwAtHostCtlSnooping.description: Controls AARP Snooping on the router port for which the entry exists. Given the AARP protocol is enabled, setting nwAtHostCtlIfSnooping to enabled (3) turns on AARP Snooping. When AARP Snooping is enabled the source AppleTalk and physical addresses of all AARP packets received on the router port are added to the AARP Table.

nwAtHostCtlProxy.name: nwAtHostCtlProxy
nwAtHostCtlProxy.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs. Setting this object has no effect.

nwAtHostCtlCacheMax.name: nwAtHostCtlCacheMax
nwAtHostCtlCacheMax.description: Indicates the maximum number of entry slots the AARP cache can consist of. nwAtHostCtlCacheMax cannot be set to less than 16. Setting this value does not allocate any memory for the cache.

nwAtHostCtlCacheSize.name: nwAtHostCtlCacheSize
nwAtHostCtlCacheSize.description: Indicates the current number of entry slots in the AARP cache on the router port for which the entry exists. The cache automatically resizes to accommodate all entries up to the maximum number of entries set by nwAtHostCtlCacheMax.

nwAtHostCtlNumStatics.name: nwAtHostCtlNumStatics
nwAtHostCtlNumStatics.description: Indicates the total number of static entries in the AARP cache on the router port for which the entry exists. Static entries remain in the cache until they are administratively removed.

nwAtHostCtlNumDynamics.name: nwAtHostCtlNumDynamics
nwAtHostCtlNumDynamics.description: Indicates the number of dynamic entries in the AARP cache on the router port for which the entry exists. Dynamic entries area added and aged out by the AARP protocol.

nwAtHostCtlCacheHits.name: nwAtHostCtlCacheHits
nwAtHostCtlCacheHits.description: Indicates the number of times an entry in the AARP cache has been used to successfully provide the physical address required to forward an AppleTalk packet on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtHostCtlCacheMisses.name: nwAtHostCtlCacheMisses
nwAtHostCtlCacheMisses.description: Indicates the number of times the physical address required to forward an AppleTalk packet has not been found in the AARP cache on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtAclValidEntries.name: nwAtAclValidEntries
nwAtAclValidEntries.description: Indicates the number of valid entries that exist in the Access Control List Table.

nwAtAclTable.name: nwAtAclTable
nwAtAclTable.description: This table contains the Access Control List information for theAppleTalk protocol. This table contains entries, each of which allows packet forwarding between source/destination pairs to be permitted or denied. The particular list is identified by the access control list ID. Each list may contain multiple entries ordered by sequence number. When a particular access control list is searched, it is searched in sequence number order and the first match found ends the search. If no match is found, access defaults to permitted.

nwAtAclEntry.name: nwAtAclEntry
nwAtAclEntry.description: Each entry contains AppleTalk source/destination access information.

nwAtAclIdentifier.name: nwAtAclIdentifier
nwAtAclIdentifier.description: This is the primary (major) index into the AppleTalk access control list table. Essentially, this identifies the access control list by a unique identifier (at least 1) and is arbitrarily assigned by the user. All entries that have the same ID belong to the same access control list.

nwAtAclSequence.name: nwAtAclSequence
nwAtAclSequence.description: This is the secondary (minor) index into the AppleTalk access control list table. This number corresponds to a sequence number used to order multiple entries within the same access control list.

nwAtAclPermission.name: nwAtAclPermission
nwAtAclPermission.description: Specifies whether access is allowed or denied between the source and destination address pairs. Note that source and destination are interchangeable when bi-directional control is selected. To remove an existing entry set invalid (2), and it will disappear after reboot.

nwAtAclMatches.name: nwAtAclMatches
nwAtAclMatches.description: Indicates the number of matches on this entry that have resulted in the access restriction permit/deny being applied as part of the forwarding process.

nwAtAclDestZone.name: nwAtAclDestZone
nwAtAclDestZone.description: Specifies the destination zone name used to compare for matches on the access control list.

nwAtAclSrcZone.name: nwAtAclSrcZone
nwAtAclSrcZone.description: Specifies the source zone to be used to compare for matches on the access control list.

nwAtEventAdminSTATUS.name: nwAtEventAdminSTATUS
nwAtEventAdminSTATUS.description: Sets the administrative state of AppleTalk event logging. Enabled (3) causes the event log to become active. Disabled (2) causes the event log to become inactive.

nwAtEventMaxEntries.name: nwAtEventMaxEntries
nwAtEventMaxEntries.description: Sets the maximum number of entries allowed in the event log table. When the number of entries reaches the value of nwAtEventMaxEntries the first (oldest) entry is deleted to allow a new entry to be added.

nwAtEventTraceAll.name: nwAtEventTraceAll
nwAtEventTraceAll.description: Enabled (3) allows logging of all event types on all router ports from all protocols and components. Disabled (2) causes the event log filter table to specify which events to log.

nwAtEventFilterTable.name: nwAtEventFilterTable
nwAtEventFilterTable.description: This table contains an entry for each event filter configured for AppleTalk Routing Service's events.

nwAtEventFilterEntry.name: nwAtEventFilterEntry
nwAtEventFilterEntry.description: Each entry describes an event filter which defines a particular type of event to be logged to the event log. The value of nwIpEventProtocol indicates the value used in either the nwRtgProtocolTable or the nwComponentTable Cabletron Routing Services MIB, which indentifies the protocol to which the entry exists.

nwAtEventFltrProtocol.name: nwAtEventFltrProtocol
nwAtEventFltrProtocol.description: Indicates the value of the Cabletron Routing Services MIB nwRtgProtocolInstance or nwComponentRtgInstance, which identifies the protocol involved in the event for which the event filter exists.

nwAtEventFltrIfNum.name: nwAtEventFltrIfNum
nwAtEventFltrIfNum.description: Specifies the router port involved in the event for which the event filter exists.

nwAtEventFltrControl.name: nwAtEventFltrControl
nwAtEventFltrControl.description: Set this value to 3 to add the entry to the event log table. Set this value to 2 to remove the entry from the event filter table.

nwAtEventFltrType.name: nwAtEventFltrType
nwAtEventFltrType.description: This 6 bit mask specifies the types of events to be logged. By default all 6 bits are set to 1, indicating that all types of events are to be logged. Setting any bit to 0 removes an event type from this field and prevents that type of event from being logged. Setting any bit to 1 adds an event type to this field and enables that type of event to be logged.

nwAtEventFltrSeverity.name: nwAtEventFltrSeverity
nwAtEventFltrSeverity.description: Specifies the level of severity an event must meet in order to be logged. Controls the amount of event logging by ignoring events of a lower priority than specified by this filter value. `Highmed' ignores only events of the lowest severity. `Highlow' logs all events highest priority through lowest. `Highest' severity causes all events except those of the highest severity to be ignored. `Highmed' severity is the default setting which causes only events of the lowest severity to be ignored. `Highlow' severity logs all events, regardless of severity.

nwAtEventFltrAction.name: nwAtEventFltrAction
nwAtEventFltrAction.description: Specifies how the events are to be logged. Logging to the `log' stores the events in the event log table (nwIpEventFltrAction). Logging to `trap' sends events out through the trap mechanism.

nwAtEventTable.name: nwAtEventTable
nwAtEventTable.description: This table contains an entry for each event that has been logged.

nwAtEventEntry.name: nwAtEventEntry
nwAtEventEntry.description: Each entry contains the information about an event that has been logged to the event table.

nwAtEventNumber.name: nwAtEventNumber
nwAtEventNumber.description: An ordinal value assigned to the event for which the log entry exists. nwAtEvnetNumber is assigned so that each event in the event log can be uniquely identified by the value of nwAtEventNumber.

nwAtEventTime.name: nwAtEventTime
nwAtEventTime.description: Indicates the time at which the event was logged to the event log

nwAtEventType.name: nwAtEventType
nwAtEventType.description: Indicates the type of event that was logged.

nwAtEventSeverity.name: nwAtEventSeverity
nwAtEventSeverity.description: Indicates the severity that was assigned to this event.

nwAtEventProtocol.name: nwAtEventProtocol
nwAtEventProtocol.description: Indicates the value of the Cabletron Routing Services MIB nwRtgProtocolInstance or nwComponentInstance which identifies the protocol or component that was involved in the event.

nwAtEventIfNum.name: nwAtEventIfNum
nwAtEventIfNum.description: Indicates the router port that was involved in the event.

nwAtEventTextString.name: nwAtEventTextString
nwAtEventTextString.description: Contains the actual text string that was logged.

nwAtNetDiagOutboundNetAddress.name: nwAtNetDiagOutboundNetAddress
nwAtNetDiagOutboundNetAddress.description: The AppleTalk Network Address of a node with which the diagnostic test will directly correspond.

nwAtNetDiagOutboundPort.name: nwAtNetDiagOutboundPort
nwAtNetDiagOutboundPort.description: An integer representing the port through which the diagnostic test will broadcast or multicast packets.

nwAtNetDiagOutboundTimeout.name: nwAtNetDiagOutboundTimeout
nwAtNetDiagOutboundTimeout.description: An integer representing the number of seconds before a diagnostic request will time out.

nwAtNetDiagOutboundRetries.name: nwAtNetDiagOutboundRetries
nwAtNetDiagOutboundRetries.description: An integer representing the number of times a request will be repeated before failure.

nwAtNetDiagOutboundATEchoType.name: nwAtNetDiagOutboundATEchoType
nwAtNetDiagOutboundATEchoType.description: The type of echo diagnostic function to initiate. Upon setting this to send EchoRequest (2), an echo request will be initiated and the value will be set to noAction (1).

nwAtNetDiagOutboundATEchoStatus.name: nwAtNetDiagOutboundATEchoStatus
nwAtNetDiagOutboundATEchoStatus.description: The current status of the echo diagnostic.

nwAtNetDiagOutboundNBPEntityObject.name: nwAtNetDiagOutboundNBPEntityObject
nwAtNetDiagOutboundNBPEntityObject.description: The entity object or wildcard object used in the NBP lookup diagnostic.

nwAtNetDiagOutboundNBPEntityType.name: nwAtNetDiagOutboundNBPEntityType
nwAtNetDiagOutboundNBPEntityType.description: The entity type or wildcard type used in the NBP lookup diagnostic.

nwAtNetDiagOutboundNBPEntityZone.name: nwAtNetDiagOutboundNBPEntityZone
nwAtNetDiagOutboundNBPEntityZone.description: The entity zone used in the NBP lookup diagnostic.

nwAtNetDiagOutboundNBPType.name: nwAtNetDiagOutboundNBPType
nwAtNetDiagOutboundNBPType.description: Specifies the type of outbound NBP diagnostic function to initiate. Upon setting this value to any value other than noAction (1) or other (10), the corresponding request will be made and the value will be set to noAction (1).

nwAtNetDiagOutboundNBPStatus.name: nwAtNetDiagOutboundNBPStatus
nwAtNetDiagOutboundNBPStatus.description: Indicates the current status of the outbound NBP diagnostic.

nwAtNetDiagOutboundRTMPType.name: nwAtNetDiagOutboundRTMPType
nwAtNetDiagOutboundRTMPType.description: The type of outbound RTMP diagnostic function to initiate. Upon setting this value to a value other than noAction(1) or other(8), the corresponding request will be initiated and the value will be set to noAction(1).

nwAtNetDiagOutboundRTMPStatus.name: nwAtNetDiagOutboundRTMPStatus
nwAtNetDiagOutboundRTMPStatus.description: The current status of the outbound RTMP diagnostic.

nwAtNetDiagOutboundRTMPNetStart.name: nwAtNetDiagOutboundRTMPNetStart
nwAtNetDiagOutboundRTMPNetStart.description: The start of the network range from the last successful outbound RTMP request or route data request.

nwAtNetDiagOutboundRTMPNetEnd.name: nwAtNetDiagOutboundRTMPNetEnd
nwAtNetDiagOutboundRTMPNetEnd.description: The end of the network range from the last successful outbound RTMP request or route data request.

nwAtNetDiagOutboundZIPType.name: nwAtNetDiagOutboundZIPType
nwAtNetDiagOutboundZIPType.description: The type of outbound ZIP diagnostic function to initiate. Upon setting this value to a value other than noAction(1) or other(8), the corresponding request will be initiated and the value will be set to noAction(1).

nwAtNetDiagOutboundZIPStatus.name: nwAtNetDiagOutboundZIPStatus
nwAtNetDiagOutboundZIPStatus.description: The current status of the outbound ZIP diagnostic.

nwAtNetDiagOutboundZIPQueryNet.name: nwAtNetDiagOutboundZIPQueryNet
nwAtNetDiagOutboundZIPQueryNet.description: The start of the network range to send ZIP query for.

nwAtNetDiagOutboundZIPQueryZone.name: nwAtNetDiagOutboundZIPQueryZone
nwAtNetDiagOutboundZIPQueryZone.description: The first zone from the last successful ZIP query.

nwAtNetDiagOutboundZIPGetNetInfoZone.name: nwAtNetDiagOutboundZIPGetNetInfoZone
nwAtNetDiagOutboundZIPGetNetInfoZone.description: The zone name to be used in a ZIP get-net-info request diagnostic.

nwAtNetDiagOutboundZIPGetNetInfoNetStart.name: nwAtNetDiagOutboundZIPGetNetInfoNetStart
nwAtNetDiagOutboundZIPGetNetInfoNetStart.description: The start of the network range from the last successful ZIP get-net-info request.

nwAtNetDiagOutboundZIPGetNetInfoNetEnd.name: nwAtNetDiagOutboundZIPGetNetInfoNetEnd
nwAtNetDiagOutboundZIPGetNetInfoNetEnd.description: The end of the network range from the last successful ZIP get-net-info request.

nwAtNetDiagOutboundZIPGetNetInfoMulticas.name: nwAtNetDiagOutboundZIPGetNetInfoMulticast
nwAtNetDiagOutboundZIPGetNetInfoMulticas.description: The data-link multicast address from the last successful ZIP get-net-info request.

nwAtNetDiagOutboundZIPGetNetInfoDefaultZ.name: nwAtNetDiagOutboundZIPGetNetInfoDefaultZone
nwAtNetDiagOutboundZIPGetNetInfoDefaultZ.description: The default zone name from the last successful ZIP get-net-info request.

nwAtportZoneTable.name: nwAtportZoneTable
nwAtportZoneTable.description: The table of zone information for non-default zones on ports.

nwAtportZoneEntry.name: nwAtportZoneEntry
nwAtportZoneEntry.description: An entry of zone information for a port.

nwAtportZonePort.name: nwAtportZonePort
nwAtportZonePort.description: An integer representing the port to which this zone belongs. The port identified by a particular value of this object is the same port as identified by the same value of nwAtportIndex.

nwAtportZoneName.name: nwAtportZoneName
nwAtportZoneName.description: A zone name configured for the AppleTalk port referred to in the corresponding entry of nwAtportZonePort. When this value is changed in a router, the router must send a zipNotify packet on the associated network.

nwAtportZoneStatus.name: nwAtportZoneStatus
nwAtportZoneStatus.description: The status of this zone entry. Setting this object to the value invalid(2) has the effect of invalidating the corresponding entry in the nwAtportZoneTable. That is, it effectively disassociates the mapping identified with said entry. It is an implementation-specific matter as to whether the agent removes an invalidated entry from the table. Accordingly, management stations must be prepared to receive from agents tabular information corresponding to entries not currently in use. Proper interpretation of such entries requires examination of the relevant nwAtportZoneStatus object.

nwAtHostMapTable.name: nwAtHostMapTable
nwAtHostMapTable.description: The Ip Address translation table used for mapping an IP address to physical address, framing, port and circuit identifier, if applicable.

nwAtHostMapEntry.name: nwAtHostMapEntry
nwAtHostMapEntry.description: Each entry contains one AtNetworkNumber to 'physical' address equivalence, including a circuit identifier if applicable. Also provided is the framing and port number required to converse with this host.

nwAtHostMapIfIndex.name: nwAtHostMapIfIndex
nwAtHostMapIfIndex.description: This is the primary (major) index into the HostMap table. This number corresponds to the index into the MIB-2 Interfaces Group which describes the IP router port for which the entry exists.

nwAtHostMapAtAddr.name: nwAtHostMapAtAddr
nwAtHostMapAtAddr.description: The AtDdpNodeAddress corresponding to the media-dependent 'physical' address and circuit identifier (if applic).

nwAtHostMapPhysAddr.name: nwAtHostMapPhysAddr
nwAtHostMapPhysAddr.description: The media-dependent 'physical' address. The value of this object is 0 for entries indicating native-wan(8) framing.

nwAtHostMapType.name: nwAtHostMapType
nwAtHostMapType.description: Setting this object to the value invalid(2) has the effect of invalidating the corresponding entry in the nwAtHostMapTable. That is, it effectively dissasociates the circuit identified with said entry from the mapping identified with said entry. It is an implementation-specific matter as to whether the agent removes an invalidated entry from the table. Accordingly, management stations must be prepared to receive tabular information from agents that corresponds to entries not currently in use. Proper interpretation of such entries requires examination of the relevant nwAtHostMapType object.

nwAtHostMapCircuitID.name: nwAtHostMapCircuitID
nwAtHostMapCircuitID.description: The identifier for the virtual circuit present on the interface. On an interface configured for Frame Relay, this number is the DLCI for the IP Address at the end of the circuit. For non-WAN interfaces, the value of this object is zero.

nwAtHostMapFraming.name: nwAtHostMapFraming
nwAtHostMapFraming.description: Specifies the framing type required to converse with the host for which this entry exists.

nwAtHostMapPortNumber.name: nwAtHostMapPortNumber
nwAtHostMapPortNumber.description: The unique value for the logical port number. It's value ranges between 1 and a maximum value which is dependent on both the number of interfaces in the system and the number of circuits present on interfaces which are of WAN type.
